  "body": "**üßê Motivation**\r\n<!-- Is your feature request related to a specific problem? Is it just a crazy idea? Tell us about it! -->\r\n\r\nWith Ownership we can get the address via `owner()` which is essential for things like getting the balance of ERC20 tokens.\r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\n<!-- Please describe your feature request in detail. -->\r\n\r\n<!-- Make sure that you have reviewed the OpenZeppelin Contracts Contributor Guidelines. -->\r\n<!-- https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md -->\r\n\r\nI'm surprised that AccessControl doesn't have a similar feature. Since roles can change ownership it wouldn't be pertinent to assign e.g. `msg.sender` to a variable in the constructor.\r\n",
